{
  "stem": "8786.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the ratio, in general, and some places, it was even worse.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Poland, I don't even want to talk about it, out of 3 and 1/2 million, we came back about 40,000.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Tornal'a, we stayed-- when my father tried to establish again his business contacts, but our root, for the business, was in Lucenec, which is about 60 kilometers more to the west from Tornal'a.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's about an hour with the train, not more than that, an hour.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's where my mother's parents, and my mother's family had a huge, big business before the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Tornal'a was just a branch of that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Lucenec, where my mother was from, is a much bigger town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Lucenec today has also about 30,000 people, hardly any Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they still have a temple, which is the most magnificent building I ever saw in a temple.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "With the rich modern city, and today there are no Jews, but because of its beauty, architectural beauty, the government keeps the-- keeps the temple, just for a show, whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father and the family did see that in Tornal'a, to establish something, would be very, very hard.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Unfortunately, we didn't have anybody to take care of the household, keep the household.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I forgot to mention that in every town, they established the congregation, the community, what they call a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] kitchen, I think it was supported by the Joint, for the survivor-- for the surviving, we call it [NON-ENGLISH]-- they called it.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Repatriated, or returned, survivors of the Holocaust had a kitchen, which was supplied or supported by the, I think, by the Joint.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every town had that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it happened that I was, yes, in Tornal'a for a few weeks, a few months maybe, a few months.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
